  <text xml:lang="ta" type="edition">
    <body>

        <div rend="parallel">
          <p xml:id="AN124.2-kilavi">talaimakaṉ ṟērppākaṟkuraittatu.</p>
          <p xml:lang="en">What HE said to driver of [his] chariot.</p>
        </div>
        <div rend="parallel">
            <lg xml:id="AN124.2">
                <l>naṉkalaṅ kaḷiṟṟoṭu naṇṇā rēnti</l>
                <l>vantutiṟai koṭuttu vaṇaṅkiṉar vaḻimoḻintu</l>
                <l>ceṉṟī keṉpa vāyiṉ vēntaṉu</l>
                <l>nilamvarut tuṟā<supplied>a</supplied> vīṇṭiya tāṉaiyō</l>
                <l>ṭiṉṟē pukutal vāyvatu naṉṟē</l>
                <l>māṭa māṉakarp pāṭamai cēkkait</l>
                <l>tuṉitīr koḷkainaṅ kātali yiṉituṟap</l>
                <l>pācaṟai varuttam vīṭa nīyu</l>
                <l>miṉṉunimirn taṉṉa poṉṉiyaṟ puṉaipaṭaik</l>
                <l>koycuvaṟ puravik kaikavar vayaṅkupaṭai</l>
                <l>vaṇpeyaṟ kaviḻnta paiṅkoṭi mullai</l>
                <l>vīka<supplied>ma</supplied>ḻ neṭuvaḻi yūtuvaṇ ṭiriyak</l>
                <l>kālai yeytak kaṭavumati mālai</l>
                <l>yanti kāvala rampaṇai yimiḻicai</l>
                <l>yaramiya viyalakat tiyampu</l>
                <l>niṟainilai ñāyi ṉeṭumati lūrē.</l>
            </lg>
            <lg xml:lang="en">
                <l>When, after talking about the way the foes had bowed, having come</l>
                <l>offering good ornaments along with elephant bulls, paying tribute, (1f.)</l>
                <l>they say “you may go”, the king’s (3)</l>
                <l>entering today itself will go well, (5)</l>
                <l>with the army that gathered, making the ground suffer, (4)</l>
                <l>– the town with long fortifications [and] bastion in a state of plenty, (16)</l>
                <l>where in the twilight the buzzing sound of the watchmen’s</l>
                <l>pretty large drums sound in the vast inside of the terraces, (14f.)</l>
                <l>and you, so that the suffering in the camp is over, (8)</l>
                <l>for our love to have something to please [her], with the intention(?) of ending [her] unrest (7)</l>
                <l>on the quiet bed in the glorious mansion with [several] stories, (6)</l>
                <l>do urge into glowing motion,</l> 
                <l>grasping [the reins?] with [your] hands, [your] horses, with trimmed manes</l>
                <l>[and] harnesses with gold decoration, that stretch out like lightning,</l>
                <l>so that [we] may arrive at evening time, (10f.+13)</l>
                <l>while humming bees retreat on the long way fragrant with blossoms (12)</l>
                <l>of jasmine in fresh creepers that opened because of the generous raining. (11)</l>
            </lg>
        </div>
    </body>
